OL,7,FMr Williams has been in prison for
OL,8,Fnearly 20 years. In 2005, he stole a
OL,9,Ftaxi and assaulted the driver.
OL,11,FHe was given what's called an
OL,12,FImprisonment for Public Protection
OL,13,F(IPP), also known as an indefinite
OL,14,Fsentence. This means he can only be
OL,15,Freleased when deemed safe enough.
OL,17,FIPPs were abolished in 2012 but not
OL,18,Fretrospectively and he is still
OL,19,Ffighting for parole.
